Reactive-PlantUML â€“ User Service Setup
=====================================

Reactive-PlantUML provides a PlantUML server as a systemd *user* service
with socket activation.

After installation, no service is started automatically.

To enable a PlantUML server instance, run as the target user:

  systemctl --user enable --now plantuml@n.socket

Replace "n" with the TCP port number you want to expose locally.
The instance name directly corresponds to the port.

Example:

  systemctl --user enable --now plantuml@8080.socket

This will expose the PlantUML server on:

  http://localhost:8080

The service starts on first access and shuts down automatically
after a period of inactivity.
